<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6EFF9B97326DADFDB4EF6EA845" authority="Schiner 1868: 273" authorityName="Schiner" authorityPageNumber="273" authorityYear="1868" box="[151,565,554,577]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Oxyphora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aberrans">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFFFF9B97326DADFDB4EC33A845" box="[151,360,554,577]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Oxyphora aberrans</emphasis>
Schiner 1868: 273
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF536EDFF9B97326DADFDD4EF6CA865" blockId="23.[151,569,554,609]" box="[151,567,586,609]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6EFF9B97326DADFDD4EF6FA865" authority=": Hering 1947: 6" authorityName="Hering" authorityPageNumber="6" authorityYear="1947" box="[151,564,586,609]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Neotephritis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aberrans">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFFFF9B97326DADFDD4ECDAA865" box="[151,385,586,609]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Neotephritis aberrans</emphasis>
: Hering 1947: 6
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF536EDFF9B97326DADFD13EE04A9F9" blockId="23.[151,1437,653,1245]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6EFF9B97326DADFD13ECB8A8A3" authority="Schiner" authorityName="Schiner" authorityYear="1868" box="[151,483,653,679]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Oxyphora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aberrans">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFFFF9B97326DADFD13EC24A8A2" box="[151,383,653,678]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Oxyphora aberrans</emphasis>
Schiner
</taxonomicName>
, currently classified in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6EFF9B97326FCDFD13E9ADA8A3" authority="Hendel (Norrbom et al. 1999)" box="[759,1270,653,679]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Neotephritis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFFFF9B97326FCDFD13EED3A8A2" box="[759,904,653,678]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Neotephritis</emphasis>
Hendel (
<bibRefCitation id="EFDB4B1CFF9B97326ECFFD13E9B7A8A3" author="Norrbom, A. L. &amp; Carroll, L. E. &amp; Thompson, F. C. &amp; White, I. M. &amp; Freidberg, A." box="[1013,1260,653,679]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" pagination="65 - 251" refId="ref42465" refString="Norrbom, A. L., Carroll, L. E., Thompson, F. C., White, I. M. &amp; Freidberg, A. (1999) Systematic database of names. In: Thompson, F. C. (Ed.), Fruit Fly Expert Identification System and Systematic Information Database. Myia (1998), 9, pp. 65 - 251, &amp; Diptera Data Dissemination Disk (CD-ROM) (1998) 1." type="journal article" year="1999">Norrbom et al. 1999</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, is here transferred to 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6EFF9B97326C3DFD2CEF7BA8C8" authority="Hering. It" authorityName="Hering. It" box="[263,544,690,716]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Homoeothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFFFF9B97326C3DFD2CECF9A8CF" box="[263,418,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Homoeothrix</emphasis>
Hering. It
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6EFF9B97326F67FD2CEE1EA8C8" authority="(Hendel)" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[605,837,690,716]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Homoeothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lindigi">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFFFF9B97326F67FD2CEF8BA8CF" box="[605,720,690,715]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. lindigi</emphasis>
(Hendel)
</taxonomicName>
, the only previously included species, differ from 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6EFF9B97326DADFD46EC73A8F5" box="[151,296,728,753]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Neotephritis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFFFF9B97326DADFD46EC73A8F5" box="[151,296,728,753]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Neotephritis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having the lateral vertical seta dark brown to black, acuminate, and similar in color and shape and more than half as long as the medial vertical seta; both orbital setae black (posterior seta not whitish and paler than anterior seta as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6EFF9B97326CD3FCBCEF21A93F" box="[489,634,802,827]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Neotephritis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFFFF9B97326CD3FCBCEF21A93F" box="[489,634,802,827]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Neotephritis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
); and vein R 
<subScript id="17CE34A8FF9B97326E28FCACEE71A944" attach="left" box="[786,810,818,832]" fontSize="6" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">4+5</subScript>
with numerous long setulae ventrally to well beyond level of crossvein dm-cu (in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6EFF9B97326CDDFCD5EF23A960" box="[487,632,843,868]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Neotephritis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFFFF9B97326CDDFCD5EF23A960" box="[487,632,843,868]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Neotephritis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
R 
<subScript id="17CE34A8FF9B97326FA9FCC5EFF6A96D" attach="left" box="[659,685,859,873]" fontSize="6" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">4+5</subScript>
is bare ventrally or has a few short setulae proximal to the level of dm-cu, most or all of them usually proximal to r-m). The male terminalia of the two species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6EFF9B97326815FCEDED95A9B6" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Homoeothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFFFF9B97326815FCEDED95A9B6" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Homoeothrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are also very similar (
<figureCitation id="13712A68FF9B97326CE4FC06EF2BA9B6" box="[478,624,920,946]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–42" captionStartId="24.[151,269,1965,1989]" captionTargetBox="[160,1417,679,1930]" captionTargetId="figure-222@24.[155,1440,670,1959]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURES 40–42. Male terminalia, Homoeothrix lindigi (Colombia: Bogota, USNMENT00213122): 40–41, epandrium and surstyli, lateral and posterior; 42, glans, dorsal." pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Figs. 40–41</figureCitation>
). The lateral surstylus has a large, triangular posterodorsal lobe, the ventral surface of which is densely setulose, the setulae projecting posteriorly. In examined species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6EFF9B97326874FC20EDBFA9F8" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Neotephritis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFFFF9B97326874FC20EDBFA9F8" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Neotephritis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the lobe is not nearly so large nor as densely setulose.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF536EDFF9B97326DFCFB96E834AE43" blockId="23.[151,1437,653,1245]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
The two species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6EFF9B97326C93FB97EF18AE26" box="[425,579,1033,1058]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Homoeothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFFFF9B97326C93FB97EF18AE26" box="[425,579,1033,1058]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Homoeothrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ in the shape and color of the posterior notopleural seta. In 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6EFF9B97326800FB97ED90AE43" authorityName="Schiner" authorityYear="1868" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Oxyphora" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aberrans">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFFFF9B97326800FB97ED90AE43" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. aberrans</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it is whitish and lanceolate, whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6EFF9B97326FA5FBB0EE54AE43" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[671,783,1070,1095]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Homoeothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lindigi">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFFFF9B97326FA5FBB0EE54AE43" box="[671,783,1070,1095]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. lindigi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
it may be slightly paler brownish, but is acuminate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3506566FF9B97326DFCFBCDEC71AED9" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BF536EDFF9B97326DFCFBCDEC71AED9" blockId="23.[151,1437,653,1245]" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">
Species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6EFF9B97326C70FBCDECBFAE68" box="[330,484,1107,1132]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Homoeothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFFFF9B97326C70FBCDECBFAE68" box="[330,484,1107,1132]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Homoeothrix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are so far known only from high elevation (&gt; 
<quantity id="4CB29B08FF9B9732693DFBCDE938AE69" box="[1031,1123,1107,1133]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" unit="m" value="2500.0">2500 m</quantity>
altitude), páramo areas of 
<collectingCountry id="F35D767DFF9B97326DADFBE6EC54AE96" box="[151,271,1144,1170]" name="Venezuela" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Venezuela</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="F35D767DFF9B97326C7DFBE6ECE4AE96" box="[327,447,1144,1170]" name="Colombia" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Colombia</collectingCountry>
. Specimens in the USNM collection that are 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6EFF9B97326EF0FBE7E961AE96" baseAuthorityName="Hendel" baseAuthorityYear="1914" box="[970,1082,1145,1170]" class="Insecta" family="Tephritidae" genus="Homoeothrix" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lindigi">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFFFF9B97326EF0FBE7E961AE96" box="[970,1082,1145,1170]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">H. lindigi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or a very similar species were reared from 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6EFF9B97326C11FB00EFDAAEBC" authority="Bonpl." authorityName="Bonpl." box="[299,641,1182,1208]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Espeletia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="grandiflora">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFFFF9B97326C11FB00EF73AEB3" box="[299,552,1182,1207]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Espeletia grandiflora</emphasis>
Bonpl.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6EFF9B97326F87FB00E93FAEBC" authority="(Standl.) Cuatr." authorityName="Cuatr." baseAuthorityName="Standl." box="[701,1124,1182,1208]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Ruilopezia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="floccosa">
<emphasis id="B93EEAFFFF9B97326F87FB00EEFEAEB3" box="[701,933,1182,1207]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="24">Ruilopezia floccosa</emphasis>
(Standl.) Cuatr.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6EFF9B9732694EFB00E9A0AEBC" box="[1140,1275,1182,1208]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Asteraceae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6EFF9B97326832FB00E8C2AEBC" authorityName="Cassini" authorityYear="1819" box="[1288,1433,1182,1208]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="tribe" tribe="Heliantheae">Heliantheae</taxonomicName>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C4A4D6EFF9B97326DADFB5DEC44AED9" box="[151,287,1219,1245]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="23" pageNumber="24" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Milleriinae">Milleriinae</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
